narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a great course. The German department at Yale has a really good program set up. (The online flashcards were an incredible resource) I would highly recommend this class to anyone wishing to improve their German and a little German history, culture, and literature as well.

Standard course that reviews basic German structure. I took it after taking a long break from German and I was able to learn everything very well because the review is very comprehensive. The films, texts and songs can be quite fun and they give you a good idea of the culture of Germany that you talk about.
I wouldn't recommend it to a grad student, because the course-load is too demanding. I would recommend my fellow grad students to get weekly tutoring and do reading on their own.
i would recommend this class. If you need to take it, then you need to take it, but everything from german 1 and 2 really come together in 3.
I'd definitely recommend this class - I feel like my German has improved so much beyond what I learned last year, and to a point where I can really use it now.
The course is great, you read German literature, listen to German songs, and watch German movies. It can get time consuming, but it's worth it.
